{
  "text": "In this study, we used allyl isothiocyanate (AIT) and cinnamaldehyde (CNAD) as model plant antimicrobial agents to assess the efficacy of MSNPs as carriers to improve their biocidal activity. AIT and CNAD are volatile oils at room temperature, with low solubility, but have both been reported to be highly antimicrobial in comparison with other classes of plant secondary metabolites [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
